Setup a basic switch topo.

A ---------
          |
B --------- SW1 ------- VMX1
          |
C ---------


A B and C are VLans. (Manually)

1.  Setup the Vlans, verify that PCs on A can talk to PCs on A, B can talk to B, and C can talk to C, and A can't talk to C.
2.  add a trunk port to SW1, and setup the router.
3.  Verify that all PCs can talk.

Create Two PCs per VLAN.

NOTE: Write an ansible playbook to configure the PCs, and the Switches.
1.  Create playbook to configure the PC
2.  Create playbook to configure the switches
3.  See if you can merge the two.
